Chairman, Senate Committee on Judiciary, Human Rights and Legal Matters, Senator Michael Opeyemi Bamidele on Thursday picked the All Progressive Congress (APC) nomination form to return to the Senate of the National Assembly, representing Ekiti Central Senatorial District. A statement issued by his media office said that Bamidele obtained the nomination form at the International Conference Center in Abuja. Bamidele, who sponsored several Bills and Motions for the advancement of the people of Ekiti Central as well as the enhancement of good governance in the  Federal Republic of Nigeria,  vowed to ensure more dividends of democracy to his people.   OPC faction, traditionalists, mourn Alaafin     Eid-el-fitri: Kwara police ban political campaigns at…     Stakeholders advocate protection of civic space   The statement reads,  “On April 27, 2022, Senator Opeyemi Bamidele picked the  Senatorial form in order to ensure more dividends of democracy to the people of Ekiti Central and enhance good governance in the Federal Republic of Nigeria. “ Within three years of Senator Bamidele in the Senate, the people of Ekiti Central and Federal Republic of Nigeria have benefited from numerous bills and motions sponsored by him and are ready to do more for the people if given a further opportunity and an extended mandate to serve. “ The ambition of Senator Bamidele is all about service to the people of Ekiti Central and Nigeria at large.”